      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i was looking at some old street maps of london and nyc tonight and something is really tripping me out. if you overlay the ley lines from the older districts in london over the grid in lower manhattan, the angles of the major thoroughfares aren't just random. they hit these specific points at almost identical degrees. like, if you follow the transit lines, they form these weird geometric shapes that centered on certain bank buildings. have u ever looked into the geometric layouts of these cities? it feels way too deliberate to be just urban planning.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
