      "content": "yeah i mean a lot of people say it's just 'random development' but it's hard to ignore when you see how perfectly the intersections line up with the specific vaults in the financial districts. it's like a signature. for instance, if you look at the way the street bends near the old exchange in london, it mirrors the angle of the approach to the stock exchange in manhattan almost perfectly. i've been trying to map out the nodes where these lines intersect... do you think there's a mathematical reason why these specific types of structures would be the anchor points for such a widespread layout?",
